# Allocation Intelligence Layer v2 — Depth-First System Design

> **Core insight from live data:** 71% of store-style allocations = exactly 2 units. 8% = 1 unit. A store cannot sell what it cannot display. This system fixes that.

---

## The Thin Allocation Problem (Root Cause)

```
Style BC-EWS6KS11238A has 309 units across 8 sizes.
Engine spreads to 184 eligible stores.
309 ÷ 184 = 1.68 units per store.
After size splitting: most stores get 0-1 per size.

Result: Every store has scraps. No store has a sellable assortment.
```

**Current system optimizes for fairness. Retail requires effectiveness.**

---

## Updated Architecture

```
┌──────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐
│  Allocation      │────▶│  PRIORITIZATION   │────▶│  Allocation      │
│  Engine          │     │  LAYER (NEW)       │     │  Engine          │
│  (score stores)  │     │                   │     │  (distribute)    │
│                  │     │  • tier stores    │     │                  │
│  eligible_stores │     │  • compute MVA    │     │  final_allocs    │
│  store_scores    │     │  • filter by      │     │                  │
│                  │     │    depth strategy  │     │                  │
└──────────────────┘     └───────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘
                                                           │
                                                           ▼
                                                   ┌──────────────────┐
                                                   │  HEALTH LAYER    │
                                                   │  (post-alloc)    │
                                                   │                  │
